    <item>
      <title>Daemon proxy configuration</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/proxy/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/proxy/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a name=&#34;httphttps-proxy&#34;&gt;&lt;!-- included for deep-links to old section --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If your organization uses a proxy server to connect to the internet, you may&#xA;need to configure the Docker daemon to use the proxy server. The daemon uses&#xA;a proxy server to access images stored on Docker Hub and other registries,&#xA;and to reach other nodes in a Docker swarm.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page describes how to configure a proxy for the Docker daemon. For&#xA;instructions on configuring proxy settings for the Docker CLI, see &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/cli/proxy/&#34;&gt;Configure&#xA;Docker CLI to use a proxy server&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Live restore</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/live-restore/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/live-restore/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;By default, when the Docker daemon terminates, it shuts down running containers.&#xA;You can configure the daemon so that containers remain running if the daemon&#xA;becomes unavailable. This functionality is called &lt;em&gt;live restore&lt;/em&gt;. The live restore&#xA;option helps reduce container downtime due to daemon crashes, planned outages,&#xA;or upgrades.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;blockquote&#xA;    &#xA;    class=&#34;px-4 border-l-4 border-blue-light dark:border-blue-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;p class=&#34;flex gap-2 items-center text-blue-light dark:text-blue-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;icon-svg pb-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M483.18-280q12.82 0 21.32-8.63 8.5-8.62 8.5-21.37v-180q0-12.75-8.68-21.38-8.67-8.62-21.5-8.62-12.82 0-21.32 8.62-8.5 8.63-8.5 21.38v180q0 12.75 8.68 21.37 8.67 8.63 21.5 8.63Zm-3.2-314q14.02 0 23.52-9.2T513-626q0-14.45-9.48-24.22-9.48-9.78-23.5-9.78t-23.52 9.78Q447-640.45 447-626q0 13.6 9.48 22.8 9.48 9.2 23.5 9.2Zm.29 514q-82.74 0-155.5-31.5Q252-143 197.5-197.5t-86-127.34Q80-397.68 80-480.5t31.5-155.66Q143-709 197.5-763t127.34-85.5Q397.68-880 480.5-880t155.66 31.5Q709-817 763-763t85.5 127Q880-563 880-480.27q0 82.74-31.5 155.5Q817-252 763-197.68q-54 54.31-127 86Q563-80 480.27-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Alternative container runtimes</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/alternative-runtimes/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/alternative-runtimes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Docker Engine uses containerd for managing the container lifecycle,&#xA;which includes creating, starting, and stopping containers.&#xA;By default, containerd uses runc as its container runtime.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34; scroll-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;what-runtimes-can-i-use&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-runtimes-can-i-use&#34;&gt;&#xA;    What runtimes can I use?&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can use any runtime that implements the containerd&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://github.com/containerd/containerd/blob/main/core/runtime/v2/README.md&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;shim API&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;Such runtimes ship with a containerd shim, and you can use them without any&#xA;additional configuration. See &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;#use-containerd-shims&#34;&gt;Use containerd shims&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
