    <item>
      <title>Configure remote access for Docker daemon</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/remote-access/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/remote-access/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;By default, the Docker daemon listens for connections on a Unix socket to accept&#xA;requests from local clients. You can configure Docker to accept requests&#xA;from remote clients by configuring it to listen on an IP address and port as well&#xA;as the Unix socket.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- prettier-ignore --&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;blockquote&#xA;    &#xA;    class=&#34;px-4 border-l-4 border-amber-light dark:border-amber-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;p class=&#34;flex gap-2 items-center text-amber-light dark:text-amber-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;icon-svg pb-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M92-120q-9 0-15.65-4.13Q69.7-128.25 66-135q-4.17-6.6-4.58-14.3Q61-157 66-165l388-670q5-8 11.5-11.5T480-850q8 0 14.5 3.5T506-835l388 670q5 8 4.58 15.7-.41 7.7-4.58 14.3-3.7 6.75-10.35 10.87Q877-120 868-120H92Zm392.18-117q12.82 0 21.32-8.68 8.5-8.67 8.5-21.5 0-12.82-8.68-21.32-8.67-8.5-21.5-8.5-12.82 0-21.32 8.68-8.5 8.67-8.5 21.5 0 12.82 8.68 21.32 8.67 8.5 21.5 8.5Zm0-111q12.82 0 21.32-8.63 8.5-8.62 8.5-21.37v-164q0-12.75-8.68-21.38-8.67-8.62-21.5-8.62-12.82 0-21.32 8.62-8.5 8.63-8.5 21.38v164q0 12.75 8.68 21.37 8.67 8.63 21.5 8.63Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Warning&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Read the daemon logs</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/logs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/logs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The daemon logs may help you diagnose problems. The logs may be saved in one of&#xA;a few locations, depending on the operating system configuration and the logging&#xA;subsystem used:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;overflow-x-auto&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;table&gt;&#xA;    &lt;thead class=&#34;bg-gray-light-100 dark:bg-gray-dark-200&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;th class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Operating system&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;            &lt;th class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Location&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;    &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Linux&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Use the command &lt;code&gt;journalctl -xu docker.service&lt;/code&gt; (or read &lt;code&gt;/var/log/syslog&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;/var/log/messages&lt;/code&gt;, depending on your Linux Distribution)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;macOS (&lt;code&gt;dockerd&lt;/code&gt; logs)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;~/Library/Containers/com.docker.docker/Data/log/vm/dockerd.log&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;macOS (&lt;code&gt;containerd&lt;/code&gt; logs)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;~/Library/Containers/com.docker.docker/Data/log/vm/containerd.log&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Windows (WSL2) (&lt;code&gt;dockerd&lt;/code&gt; logs)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;%LOCALAPPDATA%\Docker\log\vm\dockerd.log&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Windows (WSL2) (&lt;code&gt;containerd&lt;/code&gt; logs)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;%LOCALAPPDATA%\Docker\log\vm\containerd.log&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Windows (Windows containers)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td class=&#34;p-2&#34; style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Logs are in the Windows Event Log&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To view the &lt;code&gt;dockerd&lt;/code&gt; logs on macOS, open a terminal Window, and use the &lt;code&gt;tail&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;command with the &lt;code&gt;-f&lt;/code&gt; flag to &amp;quot;follow&amp;quot; the logs. Logs will be printed until you&#xA;terminate the command using &lt;code&gt;CTRL+c&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Troubleshooting the Docker daemon</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/engine/daemon/troubleshoot/</link>
